At least 92 more people have succumbed to COVID-19 related complications in South Africa on Friday. This takes the overall death toll up to 53 663 deaths. “Eastern Cape 14, Free State 3, Gauteng 12, Kwa-Zulu Natal 3, Limpopo 0, Mpumalanga 2, North West 52, Northern Cape 5 and Western Cape 1,” according to the Health Ministry Department. According to the Department of Health, 1 424 new cases were reported in the last 24 hours, bringing the cumulative number of COVID-19 cases to 1 564 355. The recoveries stand at 1 488 572, representing a recovery rate of 95%. 92 1 424 10 291 264 22 120 1 488 572 1 564 355 1 542 235 16 April 2021 53 663 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); EVDS launched Earlier on Friday, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize launched the COVID-19 Electronic Vaccination Data System for people who are aged 60 and above. Those who are eligible to receive the vaccine include essential workers, persons in congregate settings, those over 18 with comorbidities. The launch forms part of the Health Department’s preparations for the second phase of the vaccination roll-out programme. It will run from the 17th of next month. INFOGRAPHIC: What you need to know about SA’s COVID-19 Electronic Vaccination Data System Below is the infographic on the digital system: ELECTRONIC VACCINATION DATA SYSTEM Requirements to register: AGE ﻿// You must be 60 years or older to register for the vaccine. IDENTITY// You must have your ID and medical aid card (if you have one) ready before you register. CONTACT// Put in correct address, cell phone and medical aid numbers when registering. CENTRE// Once registered you will be allocated to the relevent vaccination center. sabcnews.com | SABC News Channel | SABC Radio news SOURCE: StatsSA, ﻿Finfind, Medium Term Budget 2020 How to register ﻿on the website First, make sure you have internet access. Connect to the internet and go to vaccine.enroll.health.gov.za. The system will send an SMS confirming registration for vaccination. When it is your turn to be vaccinated, you will receive SMS with a date and the place. If you have problems you may contact the COVID-19 Hotline at 0800 029 999. Source: Department of Health You will need a smartphone, a tablet or a computer. (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));